  "lecornu": {
    "name": "Sébastien Lecornu",
    "role": "Premier Ministre",
    "party": "Renaissance / Horizons",
    "bio": "The ultimate political survivor: Lecornu has been in every single government since 2017, serving as Overseas Minister, Defense Minister, and finally Prime Minister—appointed on September 9, 2025 after Bayrou was toppled by a censure vote. In a surreal twist, he resigned after just 26 days when his first cabinet was rejected, only for Macron to immediately reappoint him on October 10 to form a SECOND government—making him the PM who got fired and rehired in the same week. As Defense Minister, he signed a landmark deal with Germany, Italy and Poland for long-range cruise missiles in July 2024. Now France's fourth PM in barely a year, he embodies Macron's desperate strategy of recycling the same loyal technocrats while the political system burns around them.",
    "meme_summary": "The ultimate political survivor who somehow keeps getting promoted despite being completely forgettable—like a video game NPC who accidentally became final boss.",
    "archetype": "The technocrat soldier / The survivor",
    "best_takedown_angle": "Highlight his blandness and lack of charisma—he's a manager promoted beyond his competence. Mock the 'Fnac guy' trying to run a country.",
