  "borne": {
    "name": "Elisabeth Borne",
    "role": "Ministre de l'Éducation nationale, de l'Enseignement supérieur et de la Recherche",
    "party": "Renaissance",
    "bio": "The former PM (2022-2024) who will forever be remembered as the woman who rammed through Macron's deeply unpopular pension reform using Article 49.3 ELEVEN times, triggering France's largest street protests in decades and becoming the most-censured PM in the Fifth Republic's history. After being replaced by Gabriel Attal in January 2024, she faded into the backbenches of the National Assembly, re-elected in July 2024 in the snap elections but without a significant role. An engineer by training and the second woman to serve as French PM, she's the technocrat who took all the political bullets for Macron's reform agenda and was quietly discarded once her usefulness expired.",
    "meme_summary": "The 49.3 queen who bypassed democracy so many times it became a meme—she's the face of 'we know better than voters' governance.",
    "archetype": "The comeback technocrat / 49.3 survivor",
    "best_takedown_angle": "Mock her democratic shortcuts and bureaucratic arrogance. She represents everything wrong with technocratic governance—imposing unpopular policies without debate.",
