  "attal": {
    "name": "Gabriel Attal",
    "role": "Chef de file de Renaissance à l'Assemblée / Ancien Premier Ministre",
    "party": "Renaissance",
    "bio": "The youngest Prime Minister in French history (34 years old when appointed in January 2024) and France's first openly gay head of government—who lasted just eight months before being ousted by Macron in September 2024 after the political earthquake of the snap elections. He went from Education Minister (where he banned the abaya in schools, becoming a right-wing hero overnight) to the top job, then became the youngest ex-PM since Napoleon when Lecornu replaced him. Now heading the Renaissance parliamentary group in the Assembly, he's positioning of Macronism and himself as the future a potential 2032 presidential candidate—the 'renewal' face of a ruling party that just got trounced. The meteoric rise and fall packaged in a tailored suit, Attal represents both the promise and the chaos of the Macron era: brilliant communication, zero legislative majority, and a political future that depends entirely on what happens in 2027.",
    "meme_summary": "The boy wonder who went from banning abayas to running France in record time, then got fired in record time—the shortest PM tenure since 19th century.",
    "archetype": "The boy wonder / Rising star",
    "best_takedown_angle": "Mock his meteoric rise and fall—he was PM for less than a year. The youngest leader in French history who couldn't even finish a full term before being discarded by his own president.",
