  "retailleau": {
    "name": "Bruno Retailleau",
    "role": "Ministre de l'Intérieur",
    "party": "Les Républicains",
    "bio": "The Vendée hardliner who went from Senate to Interior Minister in September 2024 under Barnier, then kept the job through the Bayrou and Lecornu governments—becoming France's most prominent security hawk. He immediately set three priorities: controlling immigration, fighting organized crime (especially drug trafficking), and 'everyday security,' proposing restrictions on migrant healthcare access and expanding detention centers. He won the LR leadership contest against Wauquiez in May 2025, and on February 12, 2026, officially declared his candidacy for the 2027 presidential election, pledging to 'restore order in France's streets and its borders' through referenda on immigration and criminal justice. The mild-mannered Catholic conservative who talks about 'restoring authority' while looking like a provincial accountant—the gap between his tough rhetoric and his librarian appearance is meme gold.",
