  "valls": {
    "name": "Manuel Valls",
    "role": "Ministre des Outre-mer",
    "party": "Renaissance (ex-PS)",
    "bio": "The political zombie who simply will not stay dead—after his humiliating Barcelona mayoral campaign (2018-2019), failed 2022 legislative run, and years in the political wilderness, Valls made a jaw-dropping comeback as Overseas Minister (Ministre d'État) in Bayrou's December 2024 government, becoming the third-ranking member of the cabinet. His appointment was immediately met with cries of 'traitor' from the left who never forgave his shift rightward. He was thrust into crisis management when Cyclone Chido devastated Mayotte on December 14, 2024, promising 'the total engagement of the nation' and making multiple trips to France's poorest department. The former PM who used 49.3 repeatedly, who switched from PS to Macronism, who ran for mayor of Barcelona—Valls is the French political version of a cat with nine lives, now on approximately his twelfth.",
    "meme_summary": "The politician who won't take a hint—like a bad reality show contestant who keeps getting voted off but keeps returning for 'All Stars' seasons.",
    "archetype": "The comeback kid / Perennial candidate",
    "best_takedown_angle": "Mock his desperation to stay relevant and his failed Barcelona adventure. He's the guy who burned every bridge and now begs for scraps at Macron's table.",
