  "dati": {
    "name": "Rachida Dati",
    "role": "Ministre de la Culture",
    "party": "LR (divers droite)",
    "bio": "The scandal-magnetic Culture Minister who was appointed in January 2024 in what was widely seen as Macron's tactical maneuver to keep Sarkozy's camp onside—and who has since accumulated legal troubles like designer handbags. She faces trial in September 2026 for alleged corruption and influence-peddling during her time as an MEP (linked to Carlos Ghosn/Renault-Nissan), and in December 2025, police raided her home AND her Culture Ministry offices in a SEPARATE corruption probe. She also got caught failing to declare luxury jewelry when she took office. Despite all this, she's the LR-backed candidate for Paris mayor in the 2026 municipal elections, running against the left in what promises to be a wild race. The woman who was Sarkozy's Justice Minister at 42, single mother who refused to name her daughter's father (rumored to be Sarkozy himself), and now a minister under investigation WHILE serving—Dati is French politics' drama queen par excellence.",
    "meme_summary": "The reality TV star of French politics—always dressed to the nines, always in some drama, and somehow still in government after countless controversies.",
    "archetype": "The tough diva / Tabloid politician",
    "best_takedown_angle": "Mock her attention-seeking behavior and constant scandals—she treats politics like a fashion show mixed with a courtroom drama. The culture minister who brings more drama than culture.",
