    "role": "Cheffe de file RN / Candidate présidentielle 2027",
    "party": "Rassemblement National",
    "bio": "The three-time presidential candidate who was on the verge of finally winning it all—polls had her leading for 2027—until a Paris court convicted her on March 31, 2025 of embezzling EU Parliament funds (fake parliamentary assistant jobs from 2004-2016), sentencing her to four years (two suspended) and a FIVE-YEAR BAN from holding public office, effective immediately. The verdict sent shockwaves through French politics and she immediately appealed; her appeal trial ran from January 13 to February 12, 2026, with the result potentially deciding whether she can run in 2027. She played kingmaker during the 2024 political crisis, with RN's implicit support keeping Bayrou's government alive until they pulled the plug. Her conviction has accelerated the Bardella succession plan, but she insists she'll run if her appeal succeeds—and said she 'obviously' won't if convicted again.",
