  "melenchon": {
    "name": "Jean-Luc Mélenchon",
    "role": "Fondateur de La France Insoumise",
    "party": "La France Insoumise",
    "bio": "The volcanic far-left leader who engineered the Nouveau Front Populaire (NFP) alliance that unexpectedly won the most seats in the July 2024 snap elections—then watched helplessly as Macron refused to appoint an NFP prime minister. His refusal to call Hamas a terrorist organization after October 7, 2023 and his accusation that Assembly president Braun-Pivet was 'camping out in Tel Aviv to encourage a massacre' unleashed massive antisemitism accusations that fractured the French left. By 2025, the NFP was in open civil war, with Mélenchon declaring the PS had 'betrayed' the coalition after they refused to censure the Bayrou government, and LFI filing its own failed censure motion. In February 2026, he erupted after the government officially labeled LFI 'far-left' (extrême gauche), calling it 'manipulation.' Still treating every press conference like a Shakespearean monologue and every political setback like the fall of the Republic, he hasn't confirmed whether he'll run for president a fourth time in 2027.",
