  "wauquiez": {
    "name": "Laurent Wauquiez",
    "role": "Président des Républicains",
    "party": "Les Républicains",
    "bio": "The ENA-educated conservative who returned to the National Assembly in the July 2024 snap elections, immediately becoming president of the LR group (rebranded 'La Droite Républicaine') and positioning himself as kingmaker in the hung parliament. He survived the Ciotti betrayal—when LR's own president allied with the RN in June 2024, splitting the party—and emerged as the faction leader of what remained of the Gaullist right. Lost the LR presidential primary to Retailleau in May 2025, but on February 17, 2026, he endorsed Retailleau's candidacy while calling for 'a single candidate for the right' for 2027—leaving the door open for himself as the unity candidate if Retailleau falters. Still president of the powerful Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes region and widely seen as the French right's most electable moderate face, playing the long game from his Alpine stronghold.",
