  "philippe": {
    "name": "Édouard Philippe",
    "role": "Maire du Havre / Candidat à la présidentielle 2027",
    "party": "Horizons",
    "bio": "The most patient man in French politics finally showed his hand on September 3, 2024, formally announcing 'I will be a candidate in the next presidential election'—the worst-kept secret since Macron's Jupiter complex. As founder and leader of the center-right Horizons party, he's positioned himself as the 'serious adult' alternative in the post-Macron era, regularly polling as France's most popular former PM. But his 2027 campaign faces a major test with the March 2026 municipal elections in Le Havre, where rivals are threatening his mayoral stronghold—losing his home base would be a devastating blow to his presidential credibility. He appeared alongside Attal and Bayrou at Renaissance's April 2025 congress, trying to build a broad centrist coalition while maintaining enough distance from Macron's toxic brand. The beard, the calm demeanor, the Le Havre port backdrop—Philippe is essentially running as the anti-chaos candidate in France's most chaotic political era.",
    "meme_summary": "The smooth-talking ex-PM with the iconic beard who's patiently waiting for 2027 like a cat watching a mouse—France's most obvious presidential candidate in waiting.",
