  "faure": {
    "name": "Olivier Faure",
    "role": "Premier Secrétaire du Parti Socialiste",
    "party": "Parti Socialiste",
    "bio": "The PS leader who pulled off a miraculous resurrection: after steering the party through its near-death experience (Hidalgo's 1.75% in 2022), he joined the NFP alliance in 2024 and saw PS deputies become the crucial swing votes in the hung parliament. His decision NOT to censure Bayrou's government in early 2025—breaking with LFI—triggered Mélenchon's fury and officially split the NFP, with Mélenchon declaring the alliance was 'reduced by one party.' Re-elected as PS leader in 2025, Faure is now positioning the Socialists as the responsible adult left, distinct from Mélenchon's radicalism—essentially trying to rebuild social democracy from the wreckage of French politics.",
    "meme_summary": "The leader of a party that went from running France to running on fumes—the political equivalent of a Nokia phone in the iPhone era.",
