  "hidalgo": {
    "name": "Anne Hidalgo",
    "role": "Maire de Paris",
    "party": "Parti Socialiste",
    "bio": "The mayor who actually DID swim in the Seine on July 17, 2024—fulfilling a years-long promise that had become a national joke—right before the Paris Olympics, in a €1.4 billion river cleanup PR stunt for the ages. She then leveraged the widely praised 2024 Olympics to rehabilitate her battered image after her catastrophic 2022 presidential campaign (1.75% of the vote, worst PS result in history). In November 2024, she confirmed she will NOT run for a third term as Paris mayor in the 2026 municipal elections, opening up one of France's most coveted political positions to a massive brawl between Dati (LR/center-right), Simonnet (LFI), and others. Her legacy includes 500km of new bike lanes, pedestrianized riverbanks, and a transformed city that Parisians either love or despise—a Seine swimming pool opened in July 2025 as the capstone of her environmental vision. The Spanish-born socialist who turned Paris into a cycling city and then peace'd out.",
    "meme_summary": "The bike lane tyrant who turned Paris into a construction zone, promised to swim in the Seine, and got fewer presidential votes than a YouTube prankster would.",
    "archetype": "The Paris bubble queen / Bike lane dictator",
    "best_takedown_angle": "Mock her Paris-centric worldview, the endless construction chaos, and the 1.75% presidential disaster. The Seine swim promise is an eternal meme goldmine.",
